        "\n",
        "## Overview\n",
        "\n",
        "This project demonstrates the creation of an interactive data dashboard for an e-commerce platform. We simulate processing a large transactional dataset, perform exploratory data analysis (EDA), and create interactive plots using `Plotly` directly within Quarto to provide actionable insights for stakeholders.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 1. Data Processing and Cleaning\n",
        "\n",
        "First, we set up our environment and generate some realistic e-commerce data to work with."
      ],
      "id": "62573216"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "message": false
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: data-setup\n",
        "\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import plotly.express as px\n",
        "from datetime import datetime, timedelta\n",
        "\n",
        "# Set seed for reproducibility\n",
        "np.random.seed(101)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate 12 months of daily sales data\n",
        "dates = [datetime(2024, 1, 1) + timedelta(days=i) for i in range(365)]\n",
        "base_sales = np.sin(np.linspace(0, 3.14, 365)) * 5000 + 10000\n",
        "noise = np.random.normal(0, 800, 365)\n",
        "daily_sales = base_sales + noise\n",
        "\n",
        "# Add seasonal spikes (e.g., Black Friday, Holidays)\n",
        "daily_sales[320:330] += np.random.normal(8000, 1000, 10)  # Late Nov\n",
        "daily_sales[345:355] += np.random.normal(6000, 800, 10)   # Pre-Xmas\n",
        "\n",
        "df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    'Date': dates,\n",
        "    'Revenue': daily_sales\n",
        "})\n",
        "\n",
        "df['Month'] = df['Date'].dt.month_name()\n",
        "df['Day_of_Week'] = df['Date'].dt.day_name()"
      ],
      "id": "data-setup",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 2. Revenue Trends Over Time\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's look at the overall revenue trajectory across the year. The interactive features allow stakeholders to zoom into specific date ranges."
      ],
      "id": "307f1e1c"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: revenue-trend\n",
        "#| fig-cap: Daily Revenue Trend (Interactive)\n",
        "\n",
        "fig = px.line(\n",
        "    df, \n",
        "    x='Date', \n",
        "    y='Revenue',\n",
        "    title='2024 Daily Revenue Forecast',\n",
        "    line_shape='spline',\n",
        "    render_mode='svg'\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig.update_traces(line_color='#0891b2', line_width=2)\n",
        "fig.update_layout(\n",
        "    xaxis_title=\"\",\n",
        "    yaxis_title=\"Revenue ($)\",\n",
        "    hovermode=\"x unified\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "revenue-trend",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 3. Weekly Seasonality\n",
        "\n",
        "Understanding which days drive the most sales helps optimise marketing spend. Here, we calculate average revenue by day of the week."
      ],
      "id": "31a58a14"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: weekly-seasonality\n",
        "#| fig-cap: Average Revenue by Day of Week\n",
        "\n",
        "# Aggregate data\n",
        "weekly_avg = df.groupby('Day_of_Week')['Revenue'].mean().reset_index()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Sort days logically\n",
        "day_order = ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday']\n",
        "weekly_avg['Day_of_Week'] = pd.Categorical(weekly_avg['Day_of_Week'], categories=day_order, ordered=True)\n",
        "weekly_avg = weekly_avg.sort_values('Day_of_Week')\n",
        "\n",
        "fig = px.bar(\n",
        "    weekly_avg,\n",
        "    x='Day_of_Week',\n",
        "    y='Revenue',\n",
        "    title='Average Revenue vs Day of the Week',\n",
        "    color='Revenue',\n",
        "    color_continuous_scale='Teal'\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig.update_layout(\n",
        "    xaxis_title=\"\",\n",
        "    yaxis_title=\"Avg Revenue ($)\",\n",
        "    coloraxis_showscale=False\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "weekly-seasonality",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
